                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13895161" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 7 Feb 2014 22:32:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems like it should be fairly easy to add as no changes are needed to any of the Type 1 parsing code, see PDF 32000 p257:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the font program for a multiple master font instance is embedded in the PDF file, it shall be an ordinary Type  1 font program, not a multiple master font program. This font program is called a snapshot of the multiple master font instance that incorporates the chosen values of the design coordinates. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895459" author="tilman" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2014 07:19:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I know, but it sounds too good to be true. So MMType1 fonts are only different when they are not embedded? (Which is unlikely because it would mean that the recipient of the file must have the font)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So either PDFontFactory.createFont() should return a PDType1Font, or the PDMMType1Font class should extend PDMMType1Font instead of PDSimpleFont (which I&apos;d prefer).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried both, and in both cases I get excellent images.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895470" author="jahewson" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2014 08:18:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s suspiciously easy! I&apos;m guessing that if the font is not embedded then the MM font  would be parsed f it were found locally. But that&apos;s not something we really need to support, lucky us.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m all in favour of  PDMMType1Font being a subclass of PDType1Font, that should be compatible with 1.8.x too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895496" author="tilman" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2014 09:38:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve committed the change in rev 1565945 for 2.0 and 1565946 for 1.8.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13987385" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 06:12:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closed after releasing PDFBox 1.8.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
